To compile without running tests and style checks::

$ ./gradlew build -PnoCheckStyle -PnoTest

Exemple to launch the FF planner:

$ java -cp build/libs/pddl4j-4.0.0.jar fr.uga.pddl4j.planners.statespace.FF benchmarks/blocksworld/domain.pddl benchmarks/blocksworld/p01.pddl


To launch the Rantanplan planner:

java -cp build/libs/pddl4j-4.0.0.jar fr.uga.pddl4j.planners.rantanplan.Rantanplan benchmarks/blocksworld/domain.pddl benchmarks/blocksworld/p01.pddl


To undersand the rantanplan planner, paper + thÃ¨se + code (rantanplan-public)


SMT solver -> cvc5
cvc5 installed in src/test/resources/SMT_solvers
Building cvc5 Java API: https://cvc5.github.io/docs/cvc5-1.0.0/api/java/java.html

Need to add the wrapper as a dependancies in the build.gradle:
dependancies: {
    ...
    // cvc5 SMT solver
    implementation files('src/test/resources/SMT_solvers/cvc5/build/install/share/java/cvc5.jar')
}

+ Need to add shared library to java.library.path

export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=$LD_LIBRARY_PATH:/home/gaspard/LIG/Code/pddl4j-rantanplan/src/test/resources/SMT_solvers/cvc5/build/install/lib


To launch cvc5 as an external executable (with test.SMT containg all the formula):
./cvc5 test.SMT --lang smt

full command to test

./gradlew build -PnoCheckStyle -PnoTest && java -cp build/libs/pddl4j-4.0.0.jar fr.uga.pddl4j.planners.rantanplan.Rantanplan benchmarks/blocksworld/domain.pddl benchmarks/blocksworld/p20.pddl

